<h1>Stuart Chaffe</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.stuartchaffe.co.uk/now/">stuartchaffe.co.uk/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Sheffield

United Kingdom
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
UX 'people', designers, researchers etc Developers; .net & php Front-end developers Stakeholders and directors.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
Putting user first, I design and build things for the web.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Firstly, I do what I do to fund my love of travel, but I'm fortunate to love what I do, too. The thought that something I design or build will be in front of hundreds of thousands of people really pushes me to do it to the best of my ability, always looking to learn and improve to be good at what I do.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
If you could see the journey whole you might never undertake it; might never dare the first step that propels you from the place you have known toward the place you know not.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Shantaram by Gregory David Roberts has been my all time favourite.
</p>

